ds4-server ignore-eos patch (for the serve-bench.py --vs ds4 arm)

Adds an "ignore_eos" bool to ds4-server's OpenAI request parsers (chat +
completions) so serve-bench.py can force fixed-length decode, matching the
--ignore-eos launch flags used on the gmlx and llama-server arms. When set:
the sampled-token EOS break and the spec-batch EOS break are skipped (finish
stays "length" at max_tokens), and the speculative eval gets a never-matching
eos_token so drafting is not EOS-capped.

Baseline: ds4 @ 80ebbc3. Apply + rebuild in your ds4 checkout:
  git apply /path/to/bench/patches/ds4-ignore-eos.patch
  make

